10914 \textcolor{comment}{/* The following macros can be used to modify the current CPU */}
10915 \textcolor{comment}{/* IPL. The definition of the macro may vary from device to   */}
10916 \textcolor{comment}{/* device.                                                    */}
10917 \textcolor{comment}{/*                                                            */}
10918 \textcolor{comment}{/* To safely set the CPU IPL, use SET\_CPU\_IPL(ipl); the       */}
10919 \textcolor{comment}{/* valid range of ipl is 0-7, it may be any expression.       */}
10920 \textcolor{comment}{/*                                                            */}
10921 \textcolor{comment}{/* SET\_CPU\_IPL(7);                                            */}
10922 \textcolor{comment}{/*                                                            */}
10923 \textcolor{comment}{/* To preserve the current IPL and save it use                */}
10924 \textcolor{comment}{/* SET\_AND\_SAVE\_CPU\_IPL(save\_to, ipl); the valid range of ipl */}
10925 \textcolor{comment}{/* is 0-7 and may be any expression, save\_to should denote    */}
10926 \textcolor{comment}{/* some temporary storage.                                    */}
10927 \textcolor{comment}{/*                                                            */}
10928 \textcolor{comment}{/* int old\_ipl;                                               */}
10929 \textcolor{comment}{/*                                                            */}
10930 \textcolor{comment}{/* SET\_AND\_SAVE\_CPU\_IPL(old\_ipl, 7);                          */}
10931 \textcolor{comment}{/*                                                            */}
10932 \textcolor{comment}{/* The IPL can be restored with RESTORE\_CPU\_IPL(saved\_to)     */}
10933 \textcolor{comment}{/*                                                            */}
10934 \textcolor{comment}{/* RESTORE\_CPU\_IPL(old\_ipl);                                  */}
10935 
\hypertarget{a00014_source_l10936}{}\hyperlink{a00014_a34d4c80d85281a545f3c7f1530803d65}{10936} \textcolor{preprocessor}{#define SET\_CPU\_IPL(ipl) \{       \(\backslash\)}
10937 \textcolor{preprocessor}{  int DISI\_save;                 \(\backslash\)}
10938 \textcolor{preprocessor}{                                 \(\backslash\)}
10939 \textcolor{preprocessor}{  DISI\_save = DISICNT;           \(\backslash\)}
10940 \textcolor{preprocessor}{  asm volatile ("disi #0x3FFF"); \(\backslash\)}
10941 \textcolor{preprocessor}{  SRbits.IPL = ipl;              \(\backslash\)}
10942 \textcolor{preprocessor}{  DISICNT = DISI\_save; \} (void) 0;}
10943 
\hypertarget{a00014_source_l10944}{}\hyperlink{a00014_a6e65280d03605e855814536f977b6e8f}{10944} \textcolor{preprocessor}{#define SET\_AND\_SAVE\_CPU\_IPL(save\_to, ipl) \{ \(\backslash\)}

10946 \textcolor{preprocessor}{  SET\_CPU\_IPL(ipl); \} (void) 0;}

10969 \textcolor{comment}{**}
10970 \textcolor{comment}{**   ICD Communication Channel Select bits:}
10971 \textcolor{comment}{**     ICS\_NONE             Reserved, do not use}
10972 \textcolor{comment}{**     ICS\_PGD3             Communicate on PGEC3 and PGED3}
10973 \textcolor{comment}{**     ICS\_PGD2             Communicate on PGEC2 and PGED2}
10974 \textcolor{comment}{**     ICS\_PGD1             Communicate on PGEC1 and PGED1}
10975 \textcolor{comment}{**}
10976 \textcolor{comment}{**   JTAG Enable bit:}
10977 \textcolor{comment}{**     JTAGEN\_OFF           JTAG is disabled}
10978 \textcolor{comment}{**     JTAGEN\_ON            JTAG is enabled}
10979 \textcolor{comment}{**}
